                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7227</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Arredondo</persName>, representing American
                        interests</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>
                        </placeName>, <lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 20, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reported <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> Government is about to order several
                    thousand Mexican soldiers from Sonora to Chihuahua. Yaqui Valley settlers fear
                    campaign against Indians may be materially affected by such action.</p>
                <pb facs="0738" n="662" xml:id="pg_662"/>
                <p>Bring to attention appropriate authorities and express the hope of this
                    Government that campaign against Yaqui Indians be vigorously prosecuted and that
                    troops be not removed from Yaqui Valley.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
